  50. ‌struct segment { char * begin; char * end; };

  52. ‌static void init_segments(void)
  53. {
  54.   extern struct segment caml_code_segments[];
  55.   char * caml_code_area_start, * caml_code_area_end;
  56.   int i;

  58.   caml_code_area_start = caml_code_segments[0].begin;
  59.   caml_code_area_end = caml_code_segments[0].end;
  60.   for (i = 1; caml_code_segments[i].begin != 0; i++) {
  61.     if (caml_code_segments[i].begin < caml_code_area_start)
  62.       caml_code_area_start = caml_code_segments[i].begin;
  63.     if (caml_code_segments[i].end > caml_code_area_end)
  64.       caml_code_area_end = caml_code_segments[i].end;
  65.   }
  66.   /* Register the code in the table of code fragments */
  67.   caml_register_code_fragment(caml_code_area_start,
  68.                               caml_code_area_end,
  69.                               DIGEST_LATER, NULL);
  70.   /* Also register the glue code written in assembly */
  71.   caml_register_code_fragment(&caml_system__code_begin,
  72.                               &caml_system__code_end,
  73.                               DIGEST_IGNORE, NULL);
  74. }

  88. ‌value caml_startup_common(char_os **argv, int pooling)
  89. {
  90.   char_os * exe_name, * proc_self_exe;
  91.   value res;

  93.   /* Determine options */
  94.   caml_parse_ocamlrunparam();

  96. #ifdef DEBUG
  97.   caml_gc_message (-1, "### OCaml runtime: debug mode ###\n");
  98. #endif
  99.   if (caml_params->cleanup_on_exit)
  100.     pooling = 1;
  101.   if (!caml_startup_aux(pooling))
  102.     return Val_unit;

  104.   caml_init_codefrag();
  105.   caml_init_locale();
  106. #ifdef _MSC_VER
  107.   caml_install_invalid_parameter_handler();
  108. #endif
  109.   caml_init_custom_operations();
  110.   caml_init_os_params();
  111.   caml_init_gc ();

  113.   /* runtime_events's init can cause a stop-the-world pause, so it must be done
  114.      after we've initialised the garbage collector */
  115.   CAML_RUNTIME_EVENTS_INIT();

  117.   init_segments();
  118.   caml_init_signals();
  119. #ifdef _WIN32
  120.   caml_win32_overflow_detection();
  121. #endif
  122.   caml_debugger_init (); /* force debugger.o stub to be linked */
  123.   exe_name = argv[0];
  124.   if (exe_name == NULL) exe_name = T("");
  125.   proc_self_exe = caml_executable_name();
  126.   if (proc_self_exe != NULL)
  127.     exe_name = proc_self_exe;
  128.   else
  129.     exe_name = caml_search_exe_in_path(exe_name);
  130.   caml_sys_init(exe_name, argv);
  131.   caml_maybe_expand_stack();
  132.   res = caml_start_program(Caml_state);
  133.   caml_terminate_signals();
  134.   return res;
  135. }

  137. ‌value caml_startup_exn(char_os **argv)
  138. {
  139.   return caml_startup_common(argv, /* pooling */ 0);
  140. }

  142. ‌void caml_startup(char_os **argv)
  143. {
  144.   value res = caml_startup_exn(argv);
  145.   if (Is_exception_result(res))
  146.     caml_fatal_uncaught_exception(Extract_exception(res));
  147. }
